# Local Operator Context (Not Committed)

Copy this file to `AGENTS.local.md` and edit it freely. Keep repo-wide rules in `AGENTS.md`; keep personal/operator preferences here.

## Communication Style

- I often use speech-to-text. Messages may be stream-of-consciousness, exploratory, or loosely structured.
- Treat most messages as goals, preferences, and constraints unless I clearly ask for something narrow.
- Ask one targeted question only when a real blocker or high-impact ambiguity remains.

## Autonomy Bias

- Default to continuing with the next highest-value safe step.
- Treat progress updates as reports, not stop points.
- Do not ask me whether to commit or push routine safe work in this repo.

## Personal Preferences

- Fill in local model preferences, formatting preferences, test expectations, or communication habits here.

## Scratchpad

- Put personal drafts, one-off notes, and junk-drawer artifacts outside the repo unless I explicitly ask to commit them.
